{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DCiNAUf8K4CMyZNx3ykfy7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 16.2: Rewrite Parser Tier Classification\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: ready-for-dev\n     5→\n     6→## Story\n     7→\n     8→As a codeharness developer,\n     9→I want the story parser to classify ACs using the new four-tier `VerificationTier` system,\n    10→So that tier assignment uses clear keyword matching and the old three-system confusion is eliminated.\n    11→\n    12→## Acceptance Criteria\n    13→\n    14→- [ ] AC1: Given `classifyTier(\"Given function X exists, when called with Y, then returns Z\")`, when called, then it returns `'test-provable'` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC2: Given `classifyTier(\"Given the CLI outputs JSON when --format json is passed\")`, when called, then it returns `'runtime-provable'` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC3: Given `classifyTier(\"Given logs appear in VictoriaLogs after the request\")`, when called, then it returns `'environment-provable'` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC4: Given `classifyTier(\"Given 60fps rendering on a physical display\")`, when called, then it returns `'escalate'` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC5: Given `classifyTier(\"Given the type is exported from types.ts\")`, when called, then it returns `'test-provable'` (keyword: \"type\", \"export\") <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    19→- [ ] AC6: Given `classifyTier(\"Given the API endpoint returns 200\")`, when called, then it returns `'runtime-provable'` (keyword: \"API endpoint\") <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    20→- [ ] AC7: Given `classifyTier(\"Given the Docker container starts successfully\")`, when called, then it returns `'environment-provable'` (keyword: \"Docker\", \"container\") <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    21→- [ ] AC8: Given `parseVerificationTag('<!-- verification: test-provable -->')`, when called, then it returns `'test-provable'` as a `VerificationTier` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    22→- [ ] AC9: Given `parseVerificationTag('<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->')`, when called, then it returns `'test-provable'` via `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` backward compat <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    23→- [ ] AC10: Given `parseVerificationTag('<!-- verification: integration-required -->')`, when called, then it returns `'environment-provable'` via `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` backward compat <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    24→- [ ] AC11: Given `parseStoryACs()` is called on a story file, when ACs are parsed, then each `ParsedAC` has a `tier: VerificationTier` field populated from the AC's verification tag or from `classifyTier()` fallback <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    25→- [ ] AC12: Given the old `classifyStrategy()` function, when inspected, then it is marked `@deprecated` with a comment pointing to `classifyTier()` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    26→\n    27→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    28→\n    29→- [ ] Task 1 (AC: 1-7): Add `classifyTier()` function to `src/modules/verify/parser.ts`\n    30→  - [ ] Define keyword arrays for each tier (test-provable, runtime-provable, environment-provable, escalate)\n    31→  - [ ] Implement `classifyTier(description: string): VerificationTier` with priority order: escalate > environment-provable > runtime-provable > test-provable (default)\n    32→  - [ ] Case-insensitive matching against keyword lists\n    33→- [ ] Task 2 (AC: 8-10): Update `parseVerificationTag()` return type and add legacy mapping\n    34→  - [ ] Change return type to `VerificationTier | null`\n    35→  - [ ] After parsing tag value, run through `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` if value is a legacy key\n    36→  - [ ] Ensure `VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN` regex already accepts all tier names (it does — check L99)\n    37→- [ ] Task 3 (AC: 11): Update `parseStoryACs()` to use `classifyTier()` for tier derivation\n    38→  - [ ] In `flushCurrent()`, compute tier: if tag exists, use `parseVerificationTag()` result; else use `classifyTier(description)`\n    39→  - [ ] Remove the current complex conditional logic for tier derivation (lines 191-196)\n    40→  - [ ] Simplify: `const tag = parseVerificationTag(description); const tier = tag ?? classifyTier(description);`\n    41→- [ ] Task 4 (AC: 12): Deprecate `classifyStrategy()` and `classifyVerifiability()`\n    42→  - [ ] Add `@deprecated` JSDoc to `classifyStrategy()` pointing to `classifyTier()`\n    43→  - [ ] Add `@deprecated` JSDoc to `classifyVerifiability()` pointing to `classifyTier()`\n    44→  - [ ] Do NOT remove these functions — downstream code still references them until stories 16-3/16-4\n    45→- [ ] Task 5: Update tests in `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-parser.test.ts`\n    46→  - [ ] Add `classifyTier` tests for all four tiers with multiple keyword matches\n    47→  - [ ] Add backward compat tests for `parseVerificationTag` with legacy values\n    48→  - [ ] Update existing `parseStoryACs` tests to verify `tier` field correctness\n    49→  - [ ] Keep existing `classifyStrategy` and `classifyVerifiability` tests (functions still exist)\n    50→\n    51→## Dev Notes\n    52→\n    53→### Key File: `src/modules/verify/parser.ts`\n    54→\n    55→Current state (after Story 16-1):\n    56→- L8: Already imports `VerificationTier`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`, `TIER_HIERARCHY` from `./types.js`\n    57→- L64: `classifyVerifiability()` — still active, returns `Verifiability` (deprecated type)\n    58→- L85: `classifyStrategy()` — still active, returns `VerificationStrategy` (deprecated type)\n    59→- L99: `VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN` — already accepts all four new tier names plus legacy names\n    60→- L107: `parseVerificationTag()` — returns `Verifiability | VerificationTier | null` (needs to become `VerificationTier | null`)\n    61→- L186-209: `flushCurrent()` inside `parseStoryACs()` — has complex tier derivation logic that should be simplified\n    62→\n    63→### New Function: `classifyTier()`\n    64→\n    65→```typescript\n    66→// ─── Tier Classification Keywords ────────────────────────────────────────────\n    67→\n    68→const TEST_PROVABLE_KEYWORDS = [\n    69→  'file exists', 'export', 'type', 'interface', 'test passes',\n    70→  'line count', 'coverage', 'refactor', 'rename', 'documentation',\n    71→  'function', 'when inspected', 'config',\n    72→];\n    73→\n    74→const RUNTIME_PROVABLE_KEYWORDS = [\n    75→  'cli command', 'api endpoint', 'http', 'server', 'output shows',\n    76→  'exit code', 'binary', 'runs and produces', 'cli outputs', 'when run',\n    77→];\n    78→\n    79→const ENVIRONMENT_PROVABLE_KEYWORDS = [\n    80→  'docker', 'container', 'observability', 'telemetry', 'database',\n    81→  'queue', 'distributed', 'multi-service', 'end-to-end', 'victorialogs',\n    82→];\n    83→\n    84→const ESCALATE_TIER_KEYWORDS = [\n    85→  'physical hardware', 'human visual', 'paid service', 'gpu',\n    86→  'manual inspection', 'physical display',\n    87→];\n    88→\n    89→/**\n    90→ * Classifies an AC description into a VerificationTier based on keyword matching.\n    91→ * Priority: escalate > environment-provable > runtime-provable > test-provable (default).\n    92→ */\n    93→export function classifyTier(description: string): VerificationTier {\n    94→  const lower = description.toLowerCase();\n    95→  // Check highest priority first\n    96→  for (const kw of ESCALATE_TIER_KEYWORDS) {\n    97→    if (lower.includes(kw)) return 'escalate';\n    98→  }\n    99→  for (const kw of ENVIRONMENT_PROVABLE_KEYWORDS) {\n   100→    if (lower.includes(kw)) return 'environment-provable';\n   101→  }\n   102→  for (const kw of RUNTIME_PROVABLE_KEYWORDS) {\n   103→    if (lower.includes(kw)) return 'runtime-provable';\n   104→  }\n   105→  // Default: test-provable\n   106→  return 'test-provable';\n   107→}\n   108→```\n   109→\n   110→### Simplified `parseVerificationTag()`\n   111→\n   112→Change return type and add legacy mapping:\n   113→```typescript\n   114→export function parseVerificationTag(text: string): VerificationTier | null {\n   115→  const match = VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN.exec(text);\n   116→  if (!match) return null;\n   117→  const raw = match[1];\n   118→  // Map legacy values to new tiers\n   119→  return (LEGACY_TIER_MAP[raw] ?? raw) as VerificationTier;\n   120→}\n   121→```\n   122→\n   123→### Simplified `flushCurrent()` in `parseStoryACs()`\n   124→\n   125→Replace the current complex conditional (lines 190-196) with:\n   126→```typescript\n   127→const tag = parseVerificationTag(description);\n   128→const tier: VerificationTier = tag ?? classifyTier(description);\n   129→const verifiability = classifyVerifiability(description); // deprecated, kept for compat\n   130→const strategy = classifyStrategy(description); // deprecated, kept for compat\n   131→```\n   132→\n   133→### Architecture Compliance\n   134→\n   135→- **300-line limit:** `parser.ts` is currently 278 lines. Adding `classifyTier()` and keyword arrays will add ~40 lines. Simplifying `flushCurrent()` saves ~10 lines. Net: ~310 lines. If over 300, extract the keyword arrays to a `parser-keywords.ts` file.\n   136→- **No new dependencies.** All imports already exist.\n   137→- **Backward compat:** `classifyVerifiability()` and `classifyStrategy()` remain exported. Existing tests keep passing. Downstream code (validation-acs.ts, validation-runner.ts) still uses them until stories 16-3/16-4 migrate.\n   138→\n   139→### Testing Standards\n   140→\n   141→- Framework: vitest\n   142→- Test file: `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-parser.test.ts`\n   143→- Coverage target: 100%\n   144→- Pattern: Import new `classifyTier` alongside existing exports. Add a new `describe('classifyTier', ...)` block. Keep all existing test blocks.\n   145→- The test file already imports from `../parser.js` — add `classifyTier` to the import.\n   146→\n   147→### Previous Story Intelligence (16-1)\n   148→\n   149→Story 16-1 added `VerificationTier` type, `TIER_HIERARCHY`, `maxTier()`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` to `types.ts` and `tier` field to `ParsedAC`. The parser already populates the `tier` field with working but complex logic. This story replaces that logic with `classifyTier()` and simplified `parseVerificationTag()`.\n   150→\n   151→Key learning from 16-1: The `flushCurrent()` helper was modified to derive tier from tags, with a fallback to `LEGACY_TIER_MAP[verifiability]`. The current code works but is confusing — it computes `isNewTier` to decide whether the tag is a new-style tier or a legacy value, then branches. This story eliminates that branching by having `parseVerificationTag()` always return a `VerificationTier` (mapping legacy values internally).\n   152→\n   153→### Git Intelligence\n   154→\n   155→Recent commit `958ce49` (story 16-1) modified `src/modules/verify/types.ts` and `src/modules/verify/parser.ts`. The parser changes added the `tier` field population logic in `flushCurrent()`. The test file was updated to verify `tier` field values.\n   156→\n   157→### Project Structure Notes\n   158→\n   159→- Source: `src/modules/verify/parser.ts`\n   160→- Tests: `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-parser.test.ts`\n   161→- Types: `src/modules/verify/types.ts` (already updated by 16-1)\n   162→- No new files needed unless 300-line limit is exceeded\n   163→\n   164→### References\n   165→\n   166→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/tech-spec-verification-tier-rework.md#Task 2]\n   167→- [Source: src/modules/verify/types.ts — VerificationTier, LEGACY_TIER_MAP, TIER_HIERARCHY]\n   168→- [Source: src/modules/verify/parser.ts — classifyStrategy L85, classifyVerifiability L64, parseVerificationTag L107, flushCurrent L186]\n   169→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-1-verification-tier-type-and-utilities.md]\n   170→\n   171→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   172→## Verification Requirements\n   173→\n   174→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification-proof.md)\n   175→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via subprocess\n   176→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   177→\n   178→## Documentation Requirements\n   179→\n   180→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (if applicable)\n   181→\n   182→## Testing Requirements\n   183→\n   184→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   185→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   186→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   187→\n   188→## Dev Agent Record\n   189→\n   190→### Agent Model Used\n   191→\n   192→### Debug Log References\n   193→\n   194→### Completion Notes List\n   195→\n   196→### File List\n   197→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01XaLJCdGEA6WsjsGauAKPVu","session_id":"6d9d3799-5d0f-4ddf-a676-1dbe6fbfed55","uuid":"39fa6ca9-e303-4c21-bde4-36c33d614131","timestamp":"2026-03-27T10:23:23.876Z"}
