{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XaLJCdGEA6WsjsGauAKPVu","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story 16-2 is complete. Here is the summary:\n\n---\n\n**Story 16-2: Rewrite Parser Tier Classification — Complete (status: review)**\n\n**What was done:**\n\n1. **Task 1 — `classifyTier()` function:** Added to `src/modules/verify/parser.ts` with four keyword arrays (TEST_PROVABLE, RUNTIME_PROVABLE, ENVIRONMENT_PROVABLE, ESCALATE_TIER) and priority-based matching.\n\n2. **Task 2 — `parseVerificationTag()` rewrite:** Changed return type to `VerificationTier | null`. Legacy values (`cli-verifiable`, `integration-required`) are now mapped through `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` internally.\n\n3. **Task 3 — `flushCurrent()` simplification:** Replaced the complex `isNewTier` branching logic with `const tier = tag ?? classifyTier(description)`. The `verifiability` and `strategy` fields are now computed independently (kept for backward compat).\n\n4. **Task 4 — Deprecation annotations:** Added `@deprecated` JSDoc to both `classifyVerifiability()` and `classifyStrategy()`, pointing to `classifyTier()`.\n\n5. **Task 5 — Tests:** Added 15 new `classifyTier` tests. Updated `parseVerificationTag` tests for legacy mapping. Updated `parseStoryACs` tests to reflect new tier derivation behavior. All existing tests preserved.\n\n6. **Architecture compliance:** Extracted keyword arrays to `src/modules/verify/parser-keywords.ts` to keep `parser.ts` at 267 lines (under 300-line limit). Exported `classifyTier` from `index.ts`. Updated `AGENTS.md`.\n\n**Files changed:**\n- `src/modules/verify/parser.ts` — core logic changes\n- `src/modules/verify/parser-keywords.ts` — new file (keyword extraction)\n- `src/modules/verify/index.ts` — added `classifyTier` export\n- `src/modules/verify/AGENTS.md` — documented new file and updated exports\n- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-parser.test.ts` — 15 new tests, updated existing tests\n- `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-2-rewrite-parser-tier-classification.md` — status update\n\n**Test results:** 3872 tests pass across 149 test files. Zero regressions.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Behavioral change in `parseStoryACs`:** The `verifiability` field is now always computed by `classifyVerifiability()` independently of the verification tag. Previously, a `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` tag would directly set `verifiability = 'integration-required'`. Now it only affects `tier` (via LEGACY_TIER_MAP). This is correct per the story spec but changes observable behavior — downstream code relying on `verifiability` reflecting the tag value will see different results. Stories 16-3/16-4 will remove the deprecated fields entirely, so this is transitional.\n- **No workarounds applied.**\n- **No TODOs left behind.**\n- **Code quality:** Clean. The keyword extraction was necessary for the 300-line limit. The `parser-keywords.ts` file is a straightforward data file with no logic.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 26\n- By tool: Bash: 6, Read: 8, Edit: 12, Grep: 2, Write: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): full test suite runs (~30 lines each), tsc check (~1 line)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 10 total reads (parser.ts read 3 times due to progressive edits)\n- Redundant operations: parser.ts was read 3 times — once for initial understanding, once after partial edits failed to match, once for the full rewrite. The full rewrite was needed because the Edit tool's string matching failed on a large multi-line replacement that had subtle whitespace differences from the accumulated edits."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a803fe19a705859f5 (use SendMessage with to: 'a803fe19a705859f5' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 80099\ntool_uses: 50\nduration_ms: 457002</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6d9d3799-5d0f-4ddf-a676-1dbe6fbfed55","uuid":"52855366-54f0-4ba9-a04f-43acd36d47ea","timestamp":"2026-03-27T10:30:55.